HEADWORD: Collidine
<hw>Col"li*dine</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>ko`lla</grk> glue.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>One of a class of
organic bases, <chform>C8H11N</chform>, usually pungent oily liquids,
belonging to the pyridine series, and obtained from bone oil, coal tar,
naphtha, and certain alkaloids.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

